Assuming you have python installed with virtualenv

1) Create a virtualenv for the project "virtualenv university_venv"
2) Activate the virtualenv "source university_venv/bin/activate"
3) Go inside the project directory "path/university"
4) Install dependencies "pip install -r requirements.txt"
5) Check your database settings in settings.py #78 and make the changes (We are using postgres)
6) Create a database with the name given in settings.py
7) run "python manage.py migrate" This will create the necessary tables
8) Create a superuser for admin panel "python manage.py createsuperuser"

We are all set now
To initiate project run "python manage.py runserver"

This will run the server on port 8000

To view data goto: localhost:8000/admin (This is the default admin panel provided with django)

To view our forms goto: localhost:8000/
